Package: inferno-kernel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Inferno distributed operating system kernel
 Inferno is a distributed operating system that provides a unified
 namespace and 9P protocol for distributed computing. This package
 provides the Inferno kernel components integrated into AGI-OS.
 .
 Key features:
  - 9P protocol implementation
  - Styx protocol support
  - Dis virtual machine
  - Limbo programming language
  - Distributed namespace
  - Vortex (Matula numbers + vorticity)
  - Morphule (agentic functions)
  - Egregore (daemon constellations)

Package: inferno-kernel-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: inferno-kernel (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Inferno kernel development files
 Development files, headers, and libraries for building applications
 that integrate with the Inferno kernel.
